00:00:00,060 --> 00:00:11,250
French astronaut Thomas Pesquet took photographs from the International Space Station, and he made a video.

2
00:00:12,490 --> 00:00:23,200
Pesquet photographed the Aurora Australis, above the southern Indian Ocean between Asia and Antarctica.

3
00:00:24,395 --> 00:00:31,835
The International Space Station was 440 kilometers above the earth.

4
00:00:33,065 --> 00:00:41,644
The aurora is a beautiful display of lights which take place at the earth´s poles.

5
00:00:42,515 --> 00:00:50,254
Aurora Borealis takes place at the North Pole, and people call it the Northern Lights.

6
00:00:51,245 --> 00:00:59,495
Aurora Australis takes place at the South Pole, and people call it the Southern Lights.

7
00:01:00,485 --> 00:01:06,635
In Latin, Aurora is a mystical name which means ´dawn´.

8
00:01:07,625 --> 00:01:17,535
People can sometimes watch the auroras from Earth, but they look much more beautiful from space.

